body:
When using a `SKGLView` and calling Snapshot appears to return a null SKImage. Switching to a `SKCanvasView` provides the expected output.

```
protected override void OnPaintSurface(SKPaintGLSurfaceEventArgs e)
{
    var snapshot = e.Surface.Snapshot();
    System.Diagnostics.Debug.WriteLine("Has Value: " + snapshot != null);
}
```
